  "texts": [
    "The results in Table 6 show that the LLMs are more susceptible to heterogeneous distributions of code embedding, where all of the LLMs except DeepSeekCoder-7B exhibit slight declines in the performance across the three Non-IID scenarios.However, the results also reveal that fine-tuning under Non-IID scenarios can outperform the IID scenario in many cases.",
    "In particular, Table 4 presents that the CodeLlama-7B model and DeepSeekCoder-7B model outperform the IID scenario under all Non-IID scenarios.",
    "Notably, in the best-performing scenario of DeepSeekCoder-7B (i.e., Medium), the model achieves a significant increase of 15.34% and 18.68% compared to the IID distribution.",
    "Mistral-7B and DeepSeekCoder-7B in the heterogeneous code complexity scenarios, as illustrated by Table 5, achieve the best repairing performance with all Non-IID distributions.",
    "The DeepSeekCoder-7B also achieves the largest increase at 19.02% and 18.40% on 𝑇𝑜𝑝@5 and 𝑇𝑜𝑝@10 under the extreme Non-IID scenario compared to the IID scenario from Table 6."
